Add Date Table 11

                      1. From the ribbon, click “Modeling” => ”New Table”

      2.      Copy  the following DAX and paste it in the formula bar

            DimDate = ADDCOLUMNS(CALENDAR(

DATE(YEAR(MIN('STD Cases'[Year])), 1, 1),
DATE(YEAR(MAX('STD Cases'[Year])), 12, 1)), "DateAsInteger",
FORMAT ( [Date], "YYYYMMDD" ), "Year", YEAR ( [Date] ),
"MonthNo", FORMAT ( [Date], "MM" ), "YearMonthNo", FORMAT ( [Date], "YYYY/MM" ),
"YearMonth", FORMAT ( [Date], "YYYY/mmm" ), "MonthShort", FORMAT ( [Date], "mmm" ),
"MonthLong", FORMAT ( [Date], "mmmm" ), "WeekNo", WEEKDAY ( [Date] ), "WeekDay", FORMAT ( [Date], "dddd" ),
"WeekDayShort", FORMAT ( [Date], "dddd" ), "Quarter", "Q" & FORMAT ( [Date], "Q" ), "YearQuarter", FORMAT ( [Date], "YYYY" ) & "/Q" & FORMAT ( [Date],"Q" )
)


      3.     After the date table is created, click the model tab and create relationship between the new “Dim date” table and “STD Cases” table

     4.     Mark the new table as a date table
